{"title_page": "Mercedes Alison Bates", "text_new": "[[File:Mercedes Bates.jpg|thumb|right|Mercedes Bates at [[Oregon State University]], 1969]]\n'''Mercedes Allison Bates''' (September 14, 1915 \u2013 August 16, 1997) was a graduate of [[Oregon State University]] most famous for her involvement in [[General Mills]], specifically the [[Betty Crocker]] division.\n\nBates was born in [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]], [[Oregon]] in September 1915.<ref>[https://search.ancestry.co.uk/cgi-bin/sse.dll?indiv=1&dbid=60901&h=24574809&tid=&pid=&usePUB=true&_phsrc=OzZ8702&_phstart=successSource Ancestry: Mercedes Allison Bates in the U.S., Social Security Applications and Claims Index, 1936-2007]</ref> she graduated with a degree in Health and Human Sciences in 1936 from Oregon State University. Bates was also a member of the [[Delta Zeta]] [[sorority]].\n\nPost graduation, Bates had a storied job history. She started working at Southern California Gas Company as a supervisor of home services. From there she began to work at Globe Mills food, which led her to start her own venture in Hollywood as an advertising food consultant. ''McCall's'' magazine recognized her understanding of family values, their strengths and weaknesses and hired her as the food editor. In 1964, Mercedes Bates became the director of the Betty Crocker division of General Mills.  By 1966 she was vice president of the division, making her the first woman officer at General Mills.  She held this position until 1983 when she retired.  \n\nBecause of her involvement with the Betty Crocker division and her desire to make the food industry recognize family values, Bates received the nickname of \"Betty Crocker.\"\n\nShe died in August 1997 at the age of 81.<ref>[http://oregonstate.edu/dept/ncs/newsarch/1997/August97/bates.htm Mercedes Bates, OSU alum known as \"Betty Crocker,\" dies] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060913232723/http://oregonstate.edu/dept/ncs/newsarch/1997/August97/bates.htm |date=2006-09-13 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20070608071801/http://alumni.oregonstate.edu/famous/b.html\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20100601161943/http://www.hhs.oregonstate.edu/hdfs/mercedes-alison-bates\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bates, Mercedes Alison}}\n[[Category:1915 births]]\n[[Category:1997 deaths]]\n[[Category:Oregon State University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Mercedes Bates.jpg|thumb|right|Mercedes Bates at [[Oregon State University]], 1969]]\n'''Mercedes Allison Bates''' (September 14, 1915 \u2013 August 16, 1997) was a graduate of [[Oregon State University]] most famous for her involvement in [[General Mills]], specifically the [[Betty Crocker]] division.\n\nBates was born in [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]], [[Oregon]] in September 1915.<ref>[https://search.ancestry.co.uk/cgi-bin/sse.dll?indiv=1&dbid=60901&h=24574809&tid=&pid=&usePUB=true&_phsrc=OzZ8702&_phstart=successSource Ancestry: Mercedes Allison Bates in the U.S., Social Security Applications and Claims Index, 1936-2007]</ref> she graduated with a degree in Health and Human Sciences in 1936 from Oregon State University. Bates was also a member of the [[Delta Zeta]] [[sorority]].\n\nPost graduation, Bates had a storied job history. She started working at Southern California Gas Company as a supervisor of home services. From there she began to work at Globe Mills food, which led her to start her own venture in Hollywood as an advertising food consultant. ''McCall's'' magazine recognized her understanding of family values, their strengths and weaknesses and hired her as the food editor. In 1964, Mercedes Bates became the director of the Betty Crocker division of General Mills.  By 1966 she was vice president of the division, making her the first woman officer at General Mills.  She held this position until 1983 when she retired.  \n\nBecause of her involvement with the Betty Crocker division and her desire to make the food industry recognize family values, Bates received the nickname of \"Betty Crocker.\"\n\nShe died in August 1997 at the age of 81.<ref>[http://oregonstate.edu/dept/ncs/newsarch/1997/August97/bates.htm Mercedes Bates, OSU alum known as \"Betty Crocker,\" dies] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060913232723/http://oregonstate.edu/dept/ncs/newsarch/1997/August97/bates.htm |date=2006-09-13 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20070608071801/http://alumni.oregonstate.edu/famous/b.html\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20100601161943/http://www.hhs.oregonstate.edu/hdfs/mercedes-alison-bates\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bates, Mercedes Alison}}\n[[Category:1916 births]]\n[[Category:1997 deaths]]\n[[Category:Oregon State University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Jkaharper", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercedes_Alison_Bates"}
{"title_page": "-land", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=October 2010}}\n\nThe [[suffix]] '''-land''' which can be found in several countries' name and country subdivisions indicates a [[toponymy]]\u2014a [[Terrestrial ecoregion|land]]. The word came via [[Germanic languages|Germanic]] \"[[wikt:land|land]].\"\n\nBelow is the list of places that ends with \"-land\" or \"Land\".\n\n{{Expand list|date=February 2011}}\n\n== Sovereign states ==\n* {{flag|Finland}}\n* {{flag|Iceland}}\n* {{flag|Ireland}}\n* {{flag|The Netherlands}}\n* {{flag|Poland}}\n* {{flag|Switzerland}}\n* {{flag|Deutschland}}\n* {{flag|Thailand}}\nDerived name:\n* {{flag|New Zealand}}\n* {{flag|Marshall Islands}}\n* {{flag|Solomon Islands}}\n\n== Sub-national administrative divisions ==\n* {{flag|Burgenland}}, [[Austria]]\n* {{flag|Queensland}}, [[Australia]]\n* {{flag|Newfoundland and Labrador}}, [[Canada]]\n* {{flag|Prince Edward Island}}, Canada\n* {{flag|Greenland}}, [[Denmark]]\n* {{flag|\u00c5land}}, Finland\n* {{flag|Rhineland-Palatinate}}, [[Germany]]\n* {{flag|Saarland}}, Germany\n* {{flag|Nagaland}}, [[India]]\n* {{flag|Flevoland}}, the Netherlands\n* {{flag|Friesland}}, the Netherlands\n* {{flag|Gelderland}}, the Netherlands\n* {{flag|Zeeland}}, the Netherlands\n* {{flag|Somaliland}}, [[Somalia]]\n* {{flag|Puntland}}, [[Somalia]]\n* {{flag|Maryland}}, [[United States]]\n* {{flag|England}}, [[United Kingdom]]\n* {{flag|Scotland}}, United Kingdom\nDerived name:\n* {{flag|North Holland}}, the Netherlands\n* {{flag|South Holland}}, the Netherlands\n* {{flag|Northern Ireland}}, United Kingdom\n* {{flag|Rhode Island}}, United States\n\n== Other places ==\n\n=== Australia ===\n{{main|Local government in Australia}}\n* [[Central Highlands Council]], Tasmania\n* [[Central Highlands Region]], Queensland\n* [[City of Moreland]], Victoria\n* [[Shire of East Gippsland]], Victoria\n* [[City of Maitland]], New South Wales\n* [[City of Nedlands]], Western Australia\n* [[Northern Midlands Council]], Tasmania\n* [[Town of Port Hedland]], Western Australia\n* [[South Gippsland Shire]], Victoria\n* [[Southern Midlands Council]], Tasmania\n* [[Tablelands Region]], Queensland\n\n;Other places\n* [[Arnhem Land]], Northern Territory\n* [[Central Highlands (Tasmania)|Central Highlands]], Tasmania\n* [[Central Queensland]]\n* [[Far North Queensland]]\n* [[Gippsland]], Victoria\n* [[Midlands (Tasmania)|Midlands]], Tasmania\n* [[Murraylands]], South Australia\n* [[New England (Australia)|New England]], New South Wales\n* [[North Queensland]]\n* [[Northern Tablelands]], New South Wales\n* [[Portland, Victoria]]\n* [[Riverland]], South Australia\n* [[South East Queensland]]\n* [[Southern Highlands, New South Wales]]\n* [[Southern Tablelands]], New South Wales\n* [[List of islands of Australia]]\n\n=== Canada ===\n;Province level\n* [[Newfoundland (island)|Newfoundland]]\n;County level\n* [[Starland County|Starland]]\n* [[Wheatland County, Alberta|Wheatland]]\n* [[Parkland County|Parkland]]\n* [[Woodlands County|Woodlands]]\n* [[Cumberland County, Nova Scotia|Cumberland]]\n* [[Westmorland County, New Brunswick|Westmorland]]\n* [[Northumberland County, New Brunswick]]\n* [[Northumberland County, Ontario]]\n* [[Welland County, Ontario|Welland]] (historic)\n\n;Town level\n* [[Daysland]]\n* [[Hartland, New Brunswick|Hartland]]\n* [[Ferryland]]\n* [[Winterland, Newfoundland and Labrador|Winterland]]\n* [[Kirkland, Quebec|Kirkland]]\n* [[Midland, Ontario|Midland]]\n* [[Choiceland]]\n* [[Luseland]]\n* [[Zealandia, Saskatchewan|Zealandia]]\n* [[Lower Mainland]]\n* [[Cape Breton Highlands]]\n* [[Welland]]\n* [[Clarence-Rockland]]\n* [[Rossland, British Columbia|Rossland]]\n* [[Sunderland, Ontario|Sunderland]]\n* [[Aroland]]\n* [[Summerland, British Columbia|Summerland]]\n* [[Peachland]]\n* [[List of islands of Canada]]\n\n=== Denmark ===\n{{main|Lands of Denmark}}\n* [[Sj\u00e6lland]] or [[Zealand (Denmark)|Zealand]]\n* [[Jylland]] or [[Jutland]]\n* [[S\u00f8nderjylland]]\n* [[Midtjylland]]\n* [[North Denmark Region|Nordjylland]]\n* [[Lolland]]/Laaland\n\n=== Finland ===\n{{main|Lands of Finland}}\n(Names in Swedish/''Names in Finnish'')\n* Nyland / ''[[Uusimaa]]''\n* [[Southwest Finland|Egentliga Finland]] / ''[[Southwest Finland|Varsinais-Suomi]]''\n* [[Tavastia Proper|Egentliga Tavastland]] / ''[[Tavastia Proper|Kanta-H\u00e4me]]''\n* Birkaland / ''[[Pirkanmaa]]''\n* P\u00e4ij\u00e4nne-Tavastland / ''[[P\u00e4ij\u00e4t-H\u00e4me]]''\n* Mellersta Finland / ''[[Keski-Suomi]]''\n* Kajanaland / ''[[Kainuu]]''\n* [[Lapland (Finland)|Lappland]] / ''Lappi''\n* [[\u00c5land]] / ''Ahvenanmaa''\n\n=== Germany ===\n{{main|Lands of Germany}}\n* A [[States of Germany|Bundesland]]\n* [[Rheinland]] ([[Rhineland]]) and [[Rheinland-Pfalz]]\n* [[Heligoland]]\n* [[Jerichower Land]]\n* [[Mansfelder Land (disambiguation)|Mansfelder Land]]\n* [[Weimarer Land]]\n* [[Altenburger Land]]\n* [[Saale-Holzland]]\n* [[Landsberg (disambiguation)|Landsberg]]\n* [[Saterland]]\n* [[Sauerland]]\n** [[Hochsauerlandkreis]]\n* [[Altes Land]]\n* [[Wendland]]\n\n=== The Netherlands ===\n;[[City]] level:\n* [[Ameland]]\n* [[Berkelland]]\n* [[Blokland (disambiguation)|Blokland]]\n* [[Dinkelland]]\n* [[Dirksland]]\n* [[Drechterland]]\n* [[Gaasterland-Sloten|Gaasterland]]\n* [[Kollumerland]]\n* [[Lansingerland]]\n* [[Lemsterland]]\n* [[Midden-Delfland]]\n* [[Montferland]]\n* [[Nieuw-Lekkerland]]\n* [[Noord-Beveland]]\n* [[Noorder-Koggenland]]\n* [[Opsterland]]\n* [[Oud-Beijerland]]\n* [[Reiderland]]\n* [[Scharsterland]]\n* [[Schouwen-Duiveland]]\n* [[Sint Annaland]]\n* [[Smallingerland]]\n* [[Steenwijkerland]]\n* [[Vlieland]]\n* [[Waterland]]\n* [[Wester-Koggenland]]\n* [[Westland, municipality of the Netherlands|Westland]]\n* [[Wormerland]]\n* [[Zwartewaterland]]\n* [[Zuid-Beveland]]\n\n=== New Zealand ===\n* [[Auckland]]\n* [[Fiordland]]\n* [[Northland Region|Northland]]\n* [[Southland Region|Southland]]\n* [[Westland District|Westland]]\n\n=== Norway ===\n{{main|Lands of Norway}}\n{| cla