 |first=Christopher J |year=2007 |title=Who was who at Waterloo: a biography of the battle |publisher=Pearson Education|isbn= 978-0-582-78405-5}}\n* {{Citation |last=Thiers|first=Adolphe |year=1862|title=Histoire du consulat et de l'empire, faisant suite \u00e0 l'Histoire de la r\u00e9volution fran\u00e7aise|location=Paris |publisher=Lheureux et Cie.|url=https://archive.org/details/histoireduconsul20thieuoft|volume=20|language=French}}\n* {{citation |last=Torfs |first=Micha\u00ebl |date=12 March 2015 |url=http://deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws.english/News/1.2267618 |title=Belgium withdraws 'controversial' Waterloo coin under French pressure, but has a plan B |work=flandersnews.be}}\n* {{citation |last=Uffindell |first=Andrew |last2=Corum| first2=Michael |year=2002 |title=On The Fields Of Glory: The Battlefields of the 1815 Campaign |publisher=Frontline Books |isbn=978-1-85367-514-0 |pages=[https://books.google.com/books?id=30uaBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA211 211], 232\u2013233}}\n* {{Citation |last=Weller |first=J. |year=1992 |title=Wellington at Waterloo |publisher=London: Greenhill Books |isbn=978-1-85367-109-8}}\n* {{Citation |last=Weller |first=J. |year=2010 |title=Wellington at Waterloo |publisher=Frontline Books |isbn=978-1-84832-5-869}}\n* {{Citation |last=Wellesley| first=Arthur |authorlink=Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington |year=1815 |chapterurl=http://www.wtj.com/archives/wellington/1815_06f.htm |chapter=Wellington's Dispatches 19 June 1815 |title=Wellington's Dispatches Peninsular and Waterloo 1808\u20131815 |publisher=War Times Journal<!-- [http://www.wtj.com/information.htm War Times Journal (Archives)] -->}}\n* {{Citation |last=White |first=John |date=14 December 2011 |url=http://www.napoleon-series.org/research/miscellaneous/c_cambronne.html |title=Cambronne's Words, Letters to ''The Times'' (June&nbsp;1932)|publisher=the Napoleon Series |editor-first=Robert |editor-last=Burnham |accessdate=14 September 2007| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070825203333/http://www.napoleon-series.org/research/miscellaneous/c_cambronne.html| archivedate=25 August 2007| url-status= live}}\n* {{Citation |last=Wood |first=Evelyn |year=1895 |title=Cavalry in the Waterloo Campaign |publisher=Samson Low, Marston and Company |place=London}}\n* {{Cite Nuttall|wstitle=Issy|mode=cs2}}\n* {{Citation |last=Wooten |first=Geoffrey |year=1993 |title=Waterloo, 1815: The Birth Of Modern Europe |series=Osprey Campaign Series |volume=15 |location=London |publisher=Reed International Books |page=42}}\n\n==Further reading==\n===Articles===\n* Anonymous. [http://napoleonistyka.atspace.com/Imperial_Guard_at_Waterloo.htm Napoleon's Guard at Waterloo 1815]\n* Bijl, Marco, [https://web.archive.org/web/20160114161435/http://home.scarlet.be/~tsh40803/8/8st.html 8th Dutch Militia] a history of the 8th Dutch Militia battalion and the Bylandt Brigade, of which it was a part, in the 1815 campaign (using original sources from the Dutch and Belgian national archives)\n<!-- article removed from web site; dead link\n* Muilwijk, Erwin. [http://home.tiscali.nl/erwinmuilwijk/index.htm Contribution of the Netherlands Mobile Army during the 1815 campaign]. Gives full account of the Dutch troops that fought at [[Battle of Quatre Bras|Quatre-Bras]], based on many unknown primary sources.-->\n* de Wit, Pierre. [http://www.waterloo-campaign.nl/ The campaign of 1815: a study]. Study of the campaign of 1815, based on sources from all participating armies.\n* {{Citation|title=The Cowards at Waterloo|url=http://www.napolun.com/mirror/napoleonistyka.atspace.com/Waterloo_Cowards.html|accessdate=23 March 2013|ref=none}} based on {{citation |last=Dellevoet|first=A. |title=Cowards at Waterloo?: A Re-Examination of Bijlandt's Dutch-Belgian Brigade in the Campaign of 1815 |year=2001|publisher=Stackpole books |ref=none}}\n\n===Books===\n* {{Citation| last=Bonaparte| first=Napoleon |year=1995 |editor1-last=Chandler |editor1-first=David G. | editor2-last=Cairnes |editor2-first=William E. 