chestra (2013)\u2014[[David DeBoor Canfield]]\n* Concerto for soprano saxophone and chamber orchestra (2014\u201315)\u2014[[Kalevi Aho]]\n\n===Alto saxophone and orchestra===\n*Duo Concertante for soprano and alto saxophone\u2014[[Jean-Baptiste Singel\u00e9e]] (1858)\n*''Divertissement espagnol''\u2014[[Charles Martin Loeffler]] (1900)\n*Rhapsody for orchestra and saxophone (1901)\u2014[[Claude Debussy]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://digitalcommons.wku.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1000&context=mus_stu_res |title=Western Kentucky University: Top Scholar |publisher=Digitalcommons.wku.edu |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref>\n*Concerto No. 1, for alto saxophone\u2014[[Paul Gilson]] (1902)\n*Concerto No 2, for alto saxophone\u2014[[Paul Gilson]] (1902)\n*''Choral vari\u00e9'', Op. 55 (1903)\u2014[[Vincent d'Indy]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classical-composers.org/comp/indy |title=Vincent d'Indy &#124; Classical Composers Database |publisher=Classical-composers.org |date= |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref>\n*''L\u00e9gende'', Op. 66 (1918)\u2014[[Florent Schmitt]]\n*[[Saxophone Concerto (Glazunov)|Concerto in E{{music|b}} major for alto saxophone]] (1934)\u2014[[Alexander Glazunov]]\n*Saxophone Concerto, Op. 14 (1934)\u2014[[Lars-Erik Larsson]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classicalsaxophonist.com/Introduction.htm |title=introduction |publisher=Classicalsaxophonist.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref>\n*[[Concertino da camera (Ibert)|Concertino da camera]] (1935)\u2014[[Jacques Ibert]]\n*''Saxo Rhapsody'' (1936)\u2014[[Eric Coates]]\n*''Scaramouche'' for alto saxophone (1937)\u2014[[Darius Milhaud]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160304112147/http://www.ohio.edu/people/jamesm1/unt/scaramouche.doc]</ref>\n*Ballade for Saxophone and Orchestra (1938)\u2014[[Frank Martin (composer)|Frank Martin]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.konstantinosandreou.com/deuxieme-ballade-an-unknown-work-of-frank-martin/ |title=\u039a\u03c9\u03bd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\